## OWASP API Security Top 10

- **API1 (BOLA)**: Verify ownership before returning/updating resources (e.g. device/profile belongs to caller).
- **API2**: Use standard auth (e.g. session/cookie or token); no custom auth in request body.
- **API3**: Whitelist allowed fields on update; reject unknown or sensitive fields.
- **API4**: Rate limit all API endpoints to prevent abuse.
- **API5**: Enforce role/permission checks for admin or sensitive operations.
- **API6**: Rate limit sensitive flows (e.g. override, config change).
- **API7 (SSRF)**: Validate and constrain URLs before server-side fetch (allowlist host/scheme).
- **API8**: Secure API config (HTTPS, correct headers, no verbose errors).
- **API9**: Document and version APIs; retire deprecated versions.
- **API10**: Validate and sanitize data from third-party APIs; set timeouts.

---

## OWASP Top 10 for GenAI

- **LLM01 (Prompt Injection)**: Isolate user input from system prompts; use templates; sanitize/validate user input.
- **LLM02 (Insecure Output)**: Treat model output as untrusted; encode/escape before rendering (e.g. no raw HTML from AI).
- **LLM03–LLM05**: Use trusted data and models; verify sources; limit prompt size and rate.
- **LLM06 (Sensitive Disclosure)**: Never send PII/secrets in prompts; redact before sending to any AI service.
- **LLM07–LLM08**: Validate plugin/agent inputs; require human approval for critical actions.
- **LLM09–LLM10**: Validate AI outputs; do not over-rely; protect model and API access.

---

## Implementation Checklist (Before Merge)

- [ ] No raw user input in queries, commands, or HTML (injection).
- [ ] Authorization checked on every sensitive action and data access (access control).
- [ ] Errors return generic messages; details only in logs (misconfiguration / exceptional conditions).
- [ ] No secrets or PII in logs or in prompts to AI (logging / GenAI).
- [ ] Dependencies pinned and reviewed (supply chain).
- [ ] Security events logged with structured attributes (logging & alerting).

